<h3 id="well-header-rwd-bgimg">Responsive background image using [data-bgimg-srcset] plugin</h3>
<p>[data-bgimg-srcset] plugin is very similar to how <code><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img#attr-srcset">srcset</a></code> attribute works. This plugin is not to be used with [data-bgimg].</p>

<pre><code>data-bgimg-srcset="image1_link 600w, image2_link 960w, image3_link 1280w"</code></pre>

<p>Within the quotation marks, the configurations are separated by a comma and each configuration consists of a link to an image and a screen width(1000w = 1000px). Make sure to leave only one space between the link and the size. If user's screen size is greater than any sizes listed in the attribute, it will automatically choose the one with the biggest size.</p>

<div class="provisional bg-cover well" data-bgimg-srcset="../../demos/tabs/img/investinourfuture.jpg 600w, ../../demos/tabs/img/flytheskies.jpg 960w, ../../demos/tabs/img/protect-environment.jpg 1280w">
	<div class="well mrgn-tp-md mrgn-bttm-md">
		<h4 class="mrgn-tp-md">Heading</h4>
		<p>Secondary title</p>
	</div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;div class="provisional bg-cover well"
	data-bgimg="../../demos/tabs/img/investinourfuture.jpg 600w,
			../../demos/tabs/img/flytheskies.jpg 960w,
			../../demos/tabs/img/protect-environment.jpg 1280w"&gt;
	&lt;div class="well mrgn-tp-md mrgn-bttm-md"&gt;
		&lt;h4 class="mrgn-tp-md"&gt;Heading&lt;/h4&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Secondary title&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>


<h3 id="well-header-rwd-bgimg">Showing random image using [data-wb-randomize] plugin</h3>
<p>Below example shows one image out of three images randomly. Refresh the page to see that the image changes.</p>
<dl>
	<dt><code>selector</code> is a required attribute. This attribute specifies the type of child components to be displayed.</dt>
	<dt><code>shuffle</code> is a boolean value and if it is true, it will shuffle the order of child components (in this example, the child components are three <code>img</code>s).</dt>
	<dt><code>toggle</code> specifies the class that will be toggled in child components and it will toggle the specified class of child components to reveal (in this example, the name of class that will be toggled is 'hide' in three <code>img</code>s).</dt>
	<dt><code>number</code> specifies the number of child components to be displayed when toggled. If it is more than the number of child components, all of them will be displayed. If empty, it is set to 1 by default.</dt>
</dt>
<div class="provisional" data-wb-randomize='{ "shuffle": true, "selector": "img", "number": 2, "toggle": "hide" }'>
	<img class="full-width hide" src="../../demos/tabs/img/investinourfuture.jpg" alt="Invest in our Future" />
	<img class="full-width hide" src="../../demos/tabs/img/flytheskies.jpg" alt="Fly the Skies" />
	<img class="full-width hide" src="../../demos/tabs/img/protect-environment.jpg" alt="Protect Environment" />
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;div class="provisional" data-wb-randomize='{&quot;shuffle&quot;:true, &quot;selector&quot;: &quot;img&quot;, &quot;number&quot;: 2, &quot;toggle&quot;: &quot;hide&quot; }'&gt;
	&lt;img class="provisional-img-example hide"
		src="../../demos/tabs/img/investinourfuture.jpg" alt="Invest in our Future" /&gt;
	&lt;img class="provisional-img-example hide"
		src="../../demos/tabs/img/flytheskies.jpg" alt="Fly the Skies" /&gt;
	&lt;img class="provisional-img-example hide"
